## Intro to Arguments
This challenge allowed us to learn the commands and its respective arguments. A bit more complicated than the previous challenge, we learnt how Linux accepts the first words as a command and the subsequent words as arguments.

### My Solution 
**Flag:** `pwn.college{k67a4WQq_cDaiotf9CPCxJaJKUd.QX3YjM1wyN1QzNzEzW}`
The first step included typing'echo hello' which printed out hello. The echo command stored that.Next we typed 'echo hello hackers' giving an argument statement to the echo command. Itthen stored the new output. Later on at the end we just typed hello hackers and got our flag to proceed to the next module.

```bash
hacker@hello~intro-to-arguments:~$ echo hello
hello
hacker@hello~intro-to-arguments:~$ echo hello hackers
hello hackers
hacker@hello~intro-to-arguments:~$ hello hackers
Success! Here is your flag:
pwn.college{Er3QjqO_HooM7j_VQgyzDPYOJUT.QX4YjM1wyN1QzNzEzW}
```

### My learnings 
We learnt the 'echo' command in the first place and how it accepts commands and argumengts as input and gives the output. 

