## Command History
This challenge allowed us to understand that and learn that the shell saves a history of every command that we invoke. 

### My Solution 
**Flag:** `pwn.college{QgjRryxrbHBOVm48tj-fW0coqEr.0lNzEzNxwyN1QzNzEzW}`
Simply by pressing the up arrow key we got our flag. 

```bash
hacker@hello~command-history:~$ the flag is pwn.college{QgjRryxrbHBOVm48tj-fW0coqEr.0lNzEzNxwyN1QzNzEzW}
```

### My learnings 
We learnt that the Linux commands are saved in history and we can access them by using the up/down aroow key. 

